# Repo facts — example (`docs/facts.md` in each repository)

Repo-specific scope (platform position, module topology, repo Jira scoping) lives in **`docs/facts.md`** inside the repository. **Machine paths belong only in `user_facts_path`** — do not add `~/…` paths to repo facts.

Resolve path via facts key **`repo_facts_rel`** (default: `docs/facts.md`).

## Load order (company repo example)

1. `user_facts_path`
2. `company_ownership_facts` when company-scoped
3. `docs/facts.md` (this file pattern)
4. repo `AGENTS.md`

## Template (copy into `<repo>/docs/facts.md`)

```markdown
# <repo-name> — Agent Facts

Repo-specific agent context. **Machine paths and workspace keys live in `user_facts_path` only**.

## Load order

1. `user_facts_path`
2. `company_ownership_facts` (when company-scoped; key in user facts)
3. `docs/facts.md` (this file)
4. `AGENTS.md`

## Core Concepts

- **Repository**: `<name>`
- **Purpose**: one-line description

## Related Jira tasks (internal scoping)

| Ticket | Relevance |
|--------|-----------|
| `PROJ-NNNN` | Primary story for current work |
```

## Facts keys (user/workspace scope)

Defined in **`user_facts_path`** only — **Workspace roots** and **Agent skill keys** tables:

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `instructions_repo` | Clone path of the playbook (Codex/Claude/Cursor entrypoints) |
| `personal_projects_root` | Root directory for personal / pet-project repositories |
| `company_projects_root` | Root directory for company work repositories |
| `company_ownership_facts` | Company inventory and team context |
| `user_facts_path` | User/workspace facts file |
| `repo_facts_rel` | Repo-specific facts file in the current repository |
